# Layout builder

JSON-driven UI via `LayoutBuilder` + per-type renderers in `renders/`.

## Item tree rules

- Root: `items: LayoutBuilderItem[]` passed to `<LayoutBuilder />`.
- Each item has `type` (discriminant) and `id` (unique string).
- Containers use `children?: LayoutBuilderItem[]`.
- Optional `condition` hides items based on layout `data` and/or live **form field values**.
- Inside forms, use `condition` on child fields to show/hide based on checkbox, switch, radio, or select:
  - `"newsletter === true"` — when checkbox/switch is checked
  - `"form.accountType === 'business'"` — when radio/select value matches
  - Hidden fields are excluded from validation and submit payload.
- Designer-only: `locked` — strip before runtime if exporting clean JSON.

## Registered types (current)

| `type` | Renderer folder | MCP skill |
|--------|-----------------|-----------|
| `div` | `renders/div` | `generate-div-json` |
| `button` | `renders/button` | `generate-button-json` |
| `card`, `card-*` | `renders/card` | `generate-card-json` |
| `dialog`, `dialog-*` | `renders/dialog` | `generate-dialog-json` |

Unknown types render an amber placeholder in dev.

## Render-specific rules

Each render has `.cursor/AGENTS.md`, rules, and a `generate-*-json` skill:

- `renders/button/.cursor/`
- `renders/card/.cursor/`
- `renders/dialog/.cursor/`
- `renders/div/.cursor/`

## Card / dialog mode rule

Both support **legacy** (flat props) and **composed** (slot children). Never mix modes on the same item — see each render's skill.

## Button JSON (MCP)

Native HTML button type is `buttonType`, not `type` (which is always `"button"`).

## Adding a new render

1. `renders/<name>/types.ts` — item type(s)
2. `renders/<name>/index.tsx` — renderer component(s)
3. Register in `types/items.ts` union + `renders/index.tsx` switch
4. Add `renders/<name>/.cursor/` (AGENTS.md, rules, `generate-<name>-json` skill) for MCP JSON generation
